text: Snodland railway station is a railway station in Snodland in Kent. The station is on the Medway Valley Line. ==Services== Train services at Snodland are run by Southeastern, They use and EMUs. The off-peak service is: * 2 trains per hour to * 2 trains per hour to via Some trains go to . Some high speed services go between London St Pancras International and Maidstone West. On Sundays, the service is hourly. ==References== Category:Railway stations in Kent
